# Cursor AI Rules for Leta Takip Project

## Project Context
- This is a Python desktop application for session and payment tracking
- Main file: `leta_app.py` (all code is in this single file, no modules)
- Version: v1.3
- Database: SQLite3
- UI: Tkinter + ttkbootstrap

## Important Notes
- DO NOT use `font` parameter in `ttk.Button` widgets (not supported)
- All code is in `leta_app.py` - no module imports from `leta_modules/`
- Database location: OS app data folder (see `CURSOR_CONTEXT.md`)
- Main data source: `seans_takvimi` table
- Use `DataPipeline` class for data synchronization

## Code Style
- Use type hints
- Follow existing code structure in `leta_app.py`
- All functions are categorized (Utils, Database, Pricing, etc.)

## When Making Changes
1. Test syntax: `python -c "import leta_app"`
2. Check for font parameter errors in ttk widgets
3. Ensure try-except blocks are properly indented
4. Update `CURSOR_CONTEXT.md` if major changes

## Common Issues
- Font errors: Remove `font` from `ttk.Button`
- Import errors: All code is in `leta_app.py`, no external modules
- Database errors: Check column existence before querying

